1. Information We Collect

MiniHabits is designed to be lightweight and privacy-friendly. We only collect the minimum information required to provide the core functionality of the app:

User-entered data: Habits you create, reminders, and progress. This data is stored locally on your device and is not shared with us.

Notifications: The app uses local notifications to remind you about your habits. These notifications are managed on your device and do not transmit data to our servers.

Optional Third-Party Services

If you enable features such as ads or analytics, the following services may collect limited data:

AdMob (Google): For displaying ads inside the app.

Firebase / Google Analytics (if implemented): For crash reports and usage analytics.

These third-party services may collect identifiers, device information, or usage statistics according to their own privacy policies.

2. How We Use Your Information

We use your information solely to:

Provide habit tracking and notification features.

Improve app performance and stability.

Display relevant ads (if applicable).

We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with any third parties.

3. Data Storage and Security

All habit and reminder data is stored locally on your device.

We do not operate external servers to store your personal data.

If you uninstall the app, all local data is deleted from your device.

4. Children‚Äôs Privacy

MiniHabits is not directed to children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

5. Your Privacy Rights

Depending on your region, you may have rights regarding your personal information, including:

Accessing or deleting your local data.

Opting out of personalized ads (via your device settings).

